INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2360','letter','1791-12-18','Philadelphia','PA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Prevost','','Will it not be possible for you to meet me at Trenton, that we may travel together to New York? If you assent to this, I will name a day. Yet do not expose your health.','ltr_aab2360.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2361','letter','1791-12-27','Philadelphia','PA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Prevost','','If I had, before I left New York, sufficiently reflected on the subject, I would never have consented to this absurd and irrational mode of life.','ltr_aab2361.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2362','letter','1792-01-02','Philadelphia','PA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Prevost','','Mr. Trumbull is good enough to engage to deliver this.','ltr_aab2362.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2363','letter','1792-02-19','Philadelphia','PA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Prevost','','You may expect a host of such falsehoods as that about the Indian war. I have not been offered any command.','ltr_aab2363.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2364','letter','1792-08-05','Albany','NY','US','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','I have received your letter, which is very short, and says not one word of your mamma\'s health. You talk of going to WestChester, but do not say when or how.','ltr_aab2364.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2365','letter','1792-10-08','West Chester','PA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','I rose up suddenly from the sofa, and rubbing my head--What book shall I buy for her? said I to myself. She reads so much and so rapidly that it is not easy to find proper and amusing French books for her','ltr_aab2365.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2367','letter','1792-06-15','New York','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Jacob','De Lamater','','You will, before this can reach you, have heard of the event of the late election. Some questions having arisen among the canvassers respecting the returns from Clinton, Otsego, and Tioga, they requested the advice of Mr. King and myself.','ltr_aab2367.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2368','letter','1792-10-30','New York','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Jacob','De Lamater','','We may make use of both keys or ciphers, and if some of the persons or things are designated by different characters, no inconvenience will arise','ltr_aab2368.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2369','letter','1793-01-18','Philadelphia','PA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Prevost','','By the enclosed to Mr. Gurney, I have requested him to write me a letter respecting the health of the family, and Theo.\'s improvement.','ltr_aab2369.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2370','letter','1793-02-08','Philadelphia','PA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Prevost','','You may recollect that I left a memorandum of what Theo. was to learn. I hope it has been strictly attended to. ','ltr_aab2370.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2371','letter','1793-02-15','Philadelphia','PA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Prevost','','Boys and girls are generally educated much in the same way till they are eight or nine years of age, and it is admitted that girls make at least equal progress with the boys; generally, indeed, they make better.','ltr_aab2371.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2372','letter','1793-02-16','Philadelphia','PA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Prevost','','You have heard me speak of a Miss Woolstonecraft, who has written something on the French revolution; she has also written a book entitled Vindication of the rights of Woman.','ltr_aab2372.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2373','letter','1793-02-18','Philadelphia','PA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Prevost','','Deliver him the enclosed. I hope it may animate his attention; and tell him, if you think proper, that I shall be much dissatisfied if Theo.\'s progress in Latin be not very considerable at my return.','ltr_aab2373.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2374','letter','1793-02-20','Philadelphia','PA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','It would indeed have been a pity that such a letter should have been lost. There is something in the style and arrangement of the words which would have done honour to a girl of sixteen.','ltr_aab2374.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2375','letter','1793-02-24','Philadelphia','PA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','If the whole performance was your own, which I am inclined to hope and believe, it indicates an improvement in style, in knowledge of the French, and in your handwriting.','ltr_aab2375.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2376','letter','1793-12-16','Philadelphia','PA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','my time is consumed in the dull uniformity of study and attendance in Senate; but every hour of your day is interesting to me.','ltr_aab2376.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2377','letter','1793-12-24','Philadelphia','PA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Prevost','','Since being at this place I have had several conversations with Dr. Rush respecting your distressing illness, and I have reason to believe that he has given the subject some reflection.','ltr_aab2377.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2378','letter','1793-12-25','Philadelphia','PA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','When you have finished a letter, read it carefully over, and correct all the errors you can discover.','ltr_aab2378.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2379','letter','1793-12-31','Philadelphia','PA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','It is said that some few yet die of the yellow fever which lately raged here; but the disorder does not appear to be, at present, in any degree contagious','ltr_aab2379.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2380','letter','1793-12-31','Philadelphia','PA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','What -- can neither affection nor civility induce you to devote to me the small portion of time which I have required? Are authority and compulsion then the only engines by which you can be moved?','ltr_aab2380.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2381','letter','1794-01-04','Philadelphia','PA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','The account of your mamma\'s health distresses me extremely. If she does not get better soon, I will quit Congress altogether and go home.','ltr_aab2381.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2382','letter','1794-01-07','Philadelphia','PA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','You write acurate for accurate; laudnam for laudanum; intirely for entirely; this last word, indeed, is spelled both ways, but entirely is the most usual and the most proper.','ltr_aab2382.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2383','letter','1794-01-08','Philadelphia','PA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','Since the receipt of these letters I have been three times to Doctor Rush to consult him about a drink for your mamma; but not having had the good fortune to find him, have written to him on the subject.','ltr_aab2383.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2384','letter','1794-01-10','Philadelphia','PA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','I fear that you will imagine that I have been inattentive to your last request about Dr. Rush; but the truth is, I can get nothing satisfactory out of him.','ltr_aab2384.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2385','letter','1794-01-13','Philadelphia','PA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','Doctor Rush says that he cannot conceive animal food to be particularly necessary; nourishment is the great object.','ltr_aab2385.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2386','letter','1794-01-14','Philadelphia','PA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','I really think, my dear Theo., that you will be very soon beyond all verbal criticism, and that my whole attention will be presently directed to the improvement of your style.','ltr_aab2386.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2387','letter','1794-01-16','Philadelphia','PA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','I fear, my dear little girl, that my letter of the 13th imposed too much upon you; if so, dispense with what you may find too troublesome.','ltr_aab2387.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2388','letter','1794-01-23','Philadelphia','PA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','Be able, upon my arrival, to tell me the difference between an infusion and decoction; and the history, the virtues, and the botanical or medical name of the bark.','ltr_aab2388.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2389','letter','1794-02-13','Philadelphia','PA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','I despair of getting genuine Tent wine in this city. There never was a bottle of real unadulterated Tent imported here for sale. Mr. Jefferson, who had some for his own use, has left town.','ltr_aab2389.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2390','letter','1794-03-07','Philadelphia','PA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','For the last month I have been very much occupied by public business.','ltr_aab2390.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2391','letter','1794-03-31','Philadelphia','PA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','I shall in a few days (this week) send you a most beautiful assortment of flower-seeds and flowering shrubs. If I do not receive a letter from you to-morrow, I shall be out of all patience.','ltr_aab2391.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2392','letter','1794-06-07','Philadelphia','PA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','I have received my dear Theo.\'s two little, very little, French letters. The last left you tormented with headache and toothache','ltr_aab2392.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2393','letter','1794-08-04','Albany','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','It was with great pain and reluctance that I made this journey without you. But your manners are not yet quite sufficiently formed to enable you to do justice to your own character','ltr_aab2393.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2394','letter','1794-08-14','Albany','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','To the young ladies, you may pretend business or engagements: avoid, however, giving any offence to your companions. It is the manner of a refusal, much more than the refusal, which gives offence.','ltr_aab2394.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2395','letter','1794-08-16','Albany','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','Another post has arrived, and brought me no letter from you. It is the last omission which I shall readily pardon','ltr_aab2395.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2396','letter','1794-08-18','Albany','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','On the 13th you say you got nine pages in Lucian. It was, to be sure, a most surprising lesson.','ltr_aab2396.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2397','letter','1794-08-21','Troy','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','Your letters are my only consolation during this afflicting absence--for it is to me a real affliction. I have forborne to express to you my impatience, lest it should increase yours.','ltr_aab2397.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2398','letter','1794-12-21','Philadelphia','PA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','Go on, my dear girl, and you will become all that I wish.','ltr_aab2398.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2399','letter','1795-01-05','New York','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','Some weeks ago Mrs. Jackson was polite enough to call on you, with Miss Jackson and Miss Brown, who left you cards. You have never returned the visit. I beg you to do it without delay.','ltr_aab2399.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2400','letter','1795-09-14','Bristol','PA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','Saturday night I lodged at Elizabethtown, and, after two wettings, dined on Sunday with General Freelinghuysen.','ltr_aab2400.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2401','letter','1795-09-17','Philadelphia','PA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','But to return to the subject of manners, &c. I have often seen Madame at table, and other situations, pay you the utmost attention; offer you twenty civilities, while you appeared scarcely sensible','ltr_aab2401.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2402','letter','1795-09-23','Washington','MD','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','I write from the house of our friends, Law and Duncanson, where I make my home. Miss Duncanson, who is mistress of the house, is a very sprightly, sensible, ladylike woman.','ltr_aab2402.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2403','letter','1795-09-25','Washington','MD','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','Since Tuesday last I have been here much against my will; arrested by high command; performing quarantine by authority not to be questioned or controverted. In plain English, I am sick.','ltr_aab2403.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2404','letter','1796-02-08','New York','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','What will you think of the taste of New-York when I shall tell you that Miss Broadhurst is not very generally admired here?','ltr_aab2404.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2405','letter','1797-01-16','Philadelphia','PA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','When I write to you oftener than your turn, you must not let it be known, or there will be jealousy.','ltr_aab2405.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2406','letter','1797-01-23','Philadelphia','PA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','You must not puzzle all day, my dear little girl, at one hard lesson. After puzzling faithfully one hour, apply to your arithmetic, and do enough to convince the doctor that you have not been idle.','ltr_aab2406.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2407','letter','1799-01-04','Albany','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','Your despondency distresses me extremely. It is indeed unfortunate, my dear Theodosia, that we are constrained to be separated.','ltr_aab2407.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2408','letter','1799-02-11','Albany','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','You now see that a letter can come from New-York in three days; a truth which has been frequently verified by the receipt of my letters, but never before by the despatch of your own.','ltr_aab2408.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2409','letter','1800-01-26','Albany','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','The ideas, of which you are the object, that daily pass through my mind, would, if committed to writing, fill an octavo volume','ltr_aab2409.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2410','letter','1800-01-30','Albany','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','Our most humiliating errors proceed usually from inattention, and from that mental dissipation which we call heedlessness.','ltr_aab2410.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2411','letter','1797-02-01','New York','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Thomas','Morris','','I have been informed that the present sheriff of Dutchess either has resigned or will decline a reappointment, and that Platt Smith is among the candidates.','ltr_aab2411.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2412','letter','1799-10-06','New York','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','','','','I cannot refuse to the manner of your request, nor to the friendly motives which have produced it, to satisfy your inquiries with regard to Witbeck\'s bond and the Holland Company.','ltr_aab2412.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2413','letter','1800-01-02','Trenton','NJ','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','Your letters amuse me; your recovery rejoices me; your determination not to torment yourself is neither from philosophy nor spleen','ltr_aab2413.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2414','letter','1800-01-29','Albany','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','We have agreed that the cause of Le Guen shall come on next Tuesday.','ltr_aab2414.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2415','letter','1800-02-13','Albany','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','I pray you never to write to me with the mere motive of getting rid of the task. These performances always lead me to fear that all other tasks are performed in the same manner','ltr_aab2415.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2416','letter','1800-02-15','Albany','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','The argument of the cause of Le Guen is concluded. I fear that I must wait for the final decision of the court before I can leave Albany.','ltr_aab2416.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2417','letter','1800-03-05','Albany','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','But--but--these buts--how they mar all the fine theories of life!','ltr_aab2417.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2418','letter','1801-01-15','New York','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Joseph','Alston','','We are about to begin our journey to Albany.','ltr_aab2418.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2419','letter','1801-02-17','Albany','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','You are to wait in Baltimore, until I overtake you, which will be on the 28th at the latest.','ltr_aab2419.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2420','letter','1801-03-08','Washington','MD','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','Would Mr. Alston be willing to go as secretary to Chancellor Livingston?','ltr_aab2420.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2421','letter','1801-03-11','Washington','MD','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','Your Dumfries letter was received yesterday. To pass a day in Dumfries is what you could not at any time very much desire','ltr_aab2421.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2422','letter','1801-03-29','New York','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','The ferrymen pronounced it to be impossible to pass with horses, and unsafe to attempt it. By the logic of money and brandy I persuaded them to attempt it.','ltr_aab2422.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2423','letter','1801-04-15','New York','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','The ship South Carolina is now in port, and will sail on Monday next. I wish to take passage in her; but a thousand concerns of business and obstacles of various kinds appear to oppose.','ltr_aab2423.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2424','letter','1801-04-27','New York','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Joseph','Alston','','Our election commences to-morrow, and will be open for three days.','ltr_aab2424.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2425','letter','1801-04-29','New York','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','I had like to have forgotten to say a word in reply to your inquiries of matrimony, which would seem to indicate that I have no plan on the subject. Such is the fact.','ltr_aab2425.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2426','letter','1801-05-26','New York','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','Who should present himself a few days ago but A. Burr Reeve. He has come, with the consent of his father, to pass some weeks with me--more astonishment.','ltr_aab2426.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2427','letter','1801-08-20','New York','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','I was so very solicitous that you should see Niagara, that I was constantly filled with apprehension lest something might prevent it. Your letter of the 29th of July relieves me.','ltr_aab2427.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2428','letter','1801-09-18','New York','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Thomas','Morris','','Mr. Vanderlyn, the young painter from Esopus, who went about six years ago to Paris, has recently returned','ltr_aab2428.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2429','letter','1801-10-15','Albany','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Joseph','Alston','','Our Convention met on Tuesday the 13th, and will probably continue in session five or six days longer.','ltr_aab2429.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2430','letter','1801-11-03','New York','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','You made two, perhaps more conquests on your Northern tour--King Brandt and the stage-driver; both of whom have been profuse in their eulogies.','ltr_aab2430.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2431','letter','1801-11-09','New York','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','It is quite consoling to find that you will have taken the precaution to inquire the state of health before you venture your precious carcass into Charleston','ltr_aab2431.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2432','letter','1801-11-15','New York','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Joseph','Alston','','That, in New-England, men should be found hardy enough to oppose, in public speeches, the recommendation of a thanksgiving sanctioned by the usage of one hundred and fifty years','ltr_aab2432.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2433','letter','1801-11-20','New York','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','From appearance, she has been used to count her beads and work hard, and never thought of love or finery.','ltr_aab2433.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2434','letter','1801-11-26','Philadelphia','PA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','The great business, as you are pleased to call it, has brought me hither.','ltr_aab2434.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2435','letter','1801-12-08','New York','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','Your interesting letter of the 23d is this day received. It brings me to the familiar acquaintance with your amiable circle, and admits me to your fireside more than any thing you have written.','ltr_aab2435.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2436','letter','1801-12-13','New York','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Joseph','Alston','','Herewith is enclosed a duplicate of the bill of lading, specifying the articles shipped for you on board the Protectress','ltr_aab2436.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2437','letter','1801-12-15','New York','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','Yesterday Mr. Phelps, mentioned in the enclosed, delivered to me two pairs of moccasins, directed-- From Captain Joseph Brandt to Mr. and Mrs. Alston.','ltr_aab2437.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2438','letter','1802-01-12','Washington','MD','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','Your letters which greet me here are of the 2d and 20th of December only; only two.','ltr_aab2438.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2439','letter','1802-01-16','Washington','MD','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','Good venison is not to be had at this season, and to send indifferent any thing (except a wife) from New-York, would be treason.','ltr_aab2439.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2440','letter','1802-02-01','Washington','MD','US','Aaron','Burr','','Barnabas','Bidwell','','The newspapers will have shown the position of the bill now before the Senate for the repeal of the act of last session establishing a new judiciary system','ltr_aab2440.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2441','letter','1802-01-22','Washington','MD','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','Five weeks without hearing from you! Intolerable. Now I think to repose myself in sullen silence for five weeks from this date.','ltr_aab2441.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2442','letter','1802-02-02','Washington','MD','US','Aaron','Burr','','Joseph','Alston','','The repeal of the judicial system of 1801 engrosses the attention of both houses of Congress. The bill is yet before the Senate.','ltr_aab2442.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2443','letter','1802-02-02','Washington','MD','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','she talks a great deal about you; the substance of it is, that you are an ugly, little, lazy, stupid, good-for-nothing knurle, and that she is very sorry she ever wrote you a line.','ltr_aab2443.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2444','letter','1802-02-21','Washington','MD','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','A few lines from Mr. Alston, received some days before, advised me of your journey to Clifton, and of the distressing occasion.','ltr_aab2444.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2445','letter','1802-02-23','Washington','MD','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','I project, as you may have understood, a journey southward at some time, yet nameless, during the current year (or century).','ltr_aab2445.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2446','letter','1802-02-22','Washington','MD','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','You women: it is so with you all. If one wishes to exhibit the best side, one must provoke you. Gratify your wishes and expectations, or, still worse, anticipate them, and it produces a lethargy.','ltr_aab2446.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2447','letter','1802-02-26','Washington','MD','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','Your newspapers of the same date, and also of the 15th, contain particulars of the races; but so technically expressed that I comprehend nothing of it.','ltr_aab2447.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2448','letter','1802-02-27','Washington','MD','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','Last evening Eustis happened in my room while I was at Smith\'s (opposite); he saw the cover of your letter, and the few lines which it contains.','ltr_aab2448.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2449','letter','1802-03-04','Washington','MD','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','You have supposed it to be from malice that I have not written you of the adjournment and of my intentions.','ltr_aab2449.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2450','letter','1802-03-08','Washington','MD','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','I discover that you write on Sunday only; that if, by accident or mental indisposition, to which people in warm climates are liable, the business should be put off for that day, it lays over to the next Sunday','ltr_aab2450.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2451','letter','1802-03-08','Washington','MD','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','At the moment of closing your letter, this scrap of a newspaper caught my eye, and is sent for your amusement.','ltr_aab2451.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2452','letter','1802-03-08','Washington','MD','US','Aaron','Burr','','Joseph','Alston','','I learn, with a good deal of regret, that the mountain plan is abandoned; at least, that no measures are taken or meditated for its execution.','ltr_aab2452.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2453','letter','1802-03-14','Washington','MD','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','It is probable that the box went with the ship which took your first cargo; but, as no one paid the least attention to the landing of the articles, nor to compare the delivery with the invoice, it may have been left on board.','ltr_aab2453.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2454','letter','1802-03-19','Washington','MD','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','By the \"attack on Sullivan\'s Island\" was intended an attack on the plan of residence.','ltr_aab2454.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2455','letter','1802-04-05','Washington','MD','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','and thus happens what, I believe, has never before occurred, that I have two of your letters unanswered, those of the 19th and 22d, both affecting and interesting.','ltr_aab2455.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2456','letter','1802-04-12','Washington','MD','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','The instability of all human concerns has been a theme of remark for the last 4000 years.','ltr_aab2456.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2457','letter','1802-05-03','Clifton','SC','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','Unfortunately, the stage was full--not even a seat vacant for the vice-president. I am, therefore, doomed to remain here one day longer','ltr_aab2457.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2458','letter','1802-07-03','New York','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Joseph','Alston','','I desired your father to bring or send a barrel of rough rice (rice unpounded).','ltr_aab2458.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2459','letter','1802-07-05','New York','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Natalie','Sumter','','Your letter of the 22d of February, announcing your intended marriage, is this minute received.','ltr_aab2459.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2460','letter','1802-07-19','New York','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Joseph','Alston','','You will herewith receive the second book. The malice and the motives are in this so obvious, that it will tend to discredit the whole.','ltr_aab2460.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2461','letter','1802-08-02','New York','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Joseph','Alston','','The enclosed paper will give you the particulars of the affair of Swartwout and Clinton. You will perceive that the latter indirectly acknowledges that he is an agent in the calumnies against me.','ltr_aab2461.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2462','letter','1802-08-08','New York','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','By Tuesday the 9th inst. I shall be settled at Richmond Hill, ready to receive you and your incumbrances.','ltr_aab2462.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2463','letter','1802-09-08','New York','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Joseph','Alston','','The debility and loss of appetite which your wife has experienced alarmed me; yet I was totally ignorant of the cause.','ltr_aab2463.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2464','letter','1802-10-15','New York','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Joseph','Alston','','To the execution of any project, however, health is a sine qua non. Whether you can ever enjoy it in Charleston, or on Sullivan\'s Island has become a problem in my mind.','ltr_aab2464.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2465','letter','1802-11-05','New York','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Joseph','Alston','','Would Charles Lee accept the place of secretary of the Senate? It is worth twenty-three hundred dollars per annum, and not laborious.','ltr_aab2465.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2466','letter','1802-12-04','New York','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','So you arrived on the 24th, after a passage of ten days; you and the Charleston, packet on the same day.','ltr_aab2466.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2467','letter','1802-12-16','New York','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','This is not by way of reproach, for it is an unpleasant truth that, for the last six or eight weeks, the Charleston, mail has been twenty days on the way.','ltr_aab2467.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2468','letter','1803-01-26','Washington','MD','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','You know (or am I now to tell you) that you and your concerns are the highest, the dearest interest I have in this world; one in comparison with which all others are insignificant.','ltr_aab2468.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2469','letter','1803-06-02','Philadelphia','PA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','I am weary, and so must you be, of this story of Reubon and Celeste. It is, however, closed, and you will, after this letter, hear no more of it.','ltr_aab2469.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2470','letter','1803-02-23','Washington','MD','US','Aaron','Burr','','John','Coats','','I thank you for this instance of your goodness; for your friendly recollection; above all, for the justice you do to my heart and feelings.','ltr_aab2470.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2471','letter','1803-06-03','Philadelphia','PA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','Send me the number of volumes of the American Encyclopedia. I wish to complete the set, and must, therefore, know the deficiencies.','ltr_aab2471.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2472','letter','1803-06-05','Philadelphia','PA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','Pray no more apologies about your stupidity, &c., because on that subject I am perfectly informed.','ltr_aab2472.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2473','letter','1803-06-06','Philadelphia','PA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','The plot thickens, and I do not find it possible to communicate faithfully the details, without hazarding too much in case of loss of the letter.','ltr_aab2473.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2474','letter','1803-06-07','Philadelphia','PA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','As you were informed yesterday, my \'Celeste\' has gone with the family (le pere excepted) to pass a fortnight six miles from town.','ltr_aab2474.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2475','letter','1803-06-08','Philadelphia','PA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','It is finished--concluded--for ever abandoned-- \'liber sum\'. Celeste never means to marry','ltr_aab2475.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2476','letter','1803-06-10','Philadelphia','PA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','Just as I sit down to write to you I receive a note from Celeste, advising me that she is in town for a few hours, and will be happy to see me.','ltr_aab2476.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2477','letter','1803-06-16','Philadelphia','PA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','The birthday must be kept. It shall be \"honoured by my presence.\" You will therefore make your preparations','ltr_aab2477.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2478','letter','1803-07-30','New York','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','Some obscure hints in one of your letters have saddened my heart. From \'son pere\' I have merited neither suspicion nor reserve.','ltr_aab2478.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2479','letter','1803-08-01','Providence','RI','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','All those you saw when you were last here inquire about you with great civility and interest, and say pretty things of you. Don\'t be vain, madam, for I take this to be a kind of flattery to me, or to be so intended.','ltr_aab2479.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2480','letter','1803-08-06','New York','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','Lord, how I should have liked to see you dance. It is so long; how long is it? It is certain that you dance better than anybody and looked better.','ltr_aab2480.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2481','letter','1803-08-08','New York','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','But of the deaths. We die reasonably fast. Six or eight new cases reported yesterday. Of those who take the fever three fourths die.','ltr_aab2481.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2482','letter','1803-11-07','New York','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','This is the first time that I have put pen to paper at you; but I have been too busy, selling. All is sold, and well sold; not all, however. The house, outhouses, and some three or four acres remain.','ltr_aab2482.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2483','letter','1803-11-22','New York','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','Mr. Astor left with me some days ago for Mr. Alston a very beautiful map of Lower Canada, price \'ten\' dollars, and two views of Montreal and its vicinity, \'two guineas\'.','ltr_aab2483.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2484','letter','1803-12-04','Washington','MD','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','These letters are very satisfactory, except on the article of your health; of that you must speak a little more plainly.','ltr_aab2484.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2485','letter','1803-12-06','Washington','MD','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','You are a good girl to write so often. Oh, yes! I knew how much of a child you were when I sent the pretty things.','ltr_aab2485.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2486','letter','1803-12-09','Washington','MD','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','When any thing amuses me, my first thought is whether it would not also amuse you; and the pleasure is but half enjoyed until it is communicated.','ltr_aab2486.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2487','letter','1803-12-27','Washington','MD','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','Indeed, indeed, my dear little Theodosia, I will write to you very soon. Don\'t scold and pout so, and I will tell you \'how\' I visited Annapolis, and \'how\' I returned about an hour ago.','ltr_aab2487.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2488','letter','1800-07-20','New York','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Charles','Biddle','','if I had but one son, I think I should place him in the navy.','ltr_aab2488.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2489','letter','1804-01-02','Washington','MD','US','Aaron','Burr','','Charles','Biddle','','It may be satisfactory to you to know, \'officially\', that James is favourably spoken of, and is in estimation with the government.','ltr_aab2489.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2490','letter','1804-01-03','Washington','MD','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','This is only to assure you that I am in perfect health. That General Jackson is my good friend; that I have had no duel nor quarrel with anybody, and have not been wounded or hurt.','ltr_aab2490.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2491','letter','1804-01-04','Washington','MD','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','How could I forget to tell you the very important event of the marriage of Jerome Bonaparte with Miss Patterson.','ltr_aab2491.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2492','letter','1804-01-04','Washington','MD','US','Aaron','Burr','','Peggy','Gartin','','Make the master teach you arithmetic, so that you may be able to keep the accounts of the family.','ltr_aab2492.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2493','letter','1804-01-17','Washington','MD','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','I want a French translation of the Constitution of the United States, and, for the purpose, send you a copy in English. It will, I fear, be a great labour to you; but I cannot get it done here','ltr_aab2493.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2494','letter','1804-01-18','Washington','MD','US','Aaron','Burr','','Joseph','Alston','','I have been greatly flattered by the applauses bestowed on your speech at Columbia. Send me half a dozen copies. Why have you not already done it?','ltr_aab2494.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2495','letter','1804-01-20','Washington','MD','US','Aaron','Burr','','Charles','Biddle','','It is seriously my intention to visit you next week, if I can get away, which will depend a little on the state of business in Senate.','ltr_aab2495.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2496','letter','1804-01-23','Washington','MD','US','Aaron','Burr','','Charles','Biddle','','When I last wrote you (about Thursday, I think), I felt the approaches of a headache, which I concluded would be, as usual, the torment of twenty-four hours only. On the contrary, it has pursued me without intermission.','ltr_aab2496.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2497','letter','1804-01-25','Washington','MD','US','Aaron','Burr','','Natalie','Sumter','','Theodosia has given me a detailed account of yourself and your lovely little girl. All as I could wish.','ltr_aab2497.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2498','letter','1804-01-25','Washington','MD','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','I have been a week confined to my room by a headache, but there are no mortal or alarming symptoms.','ltr_aab2498.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2499','letter','1804-01-27','Washington','MD','US','Aaron','Burr','','Natalie','Sumter','','You will be proud, as a New-Yorker, to see that the first attempt to create a taste for painting and sculpture has been made in our city. We have about forty busts and groups.','ltr_aab2499.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2500','letter','1804-01-29','Washington','MD','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','There is no end to the trouble such a baggage gives me. Another thing occurs, which, forsooth, must be sent to her too.','ltr_aab2500.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2501','letter','1804-01-29','Washington','MD','US','Aaron','Burr','','A.R.','Ellery','','The bill, or project of law, herewith enclosed, is now under debate in the Senate. You will, therefore, consider it as a project merely, not yet a law.','ltr_aab2501.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2502','letter','1804-01-30','Havre de Grace','MD','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','In a former letter I told you we had eight inches snow at Washington. On Saturday last, 28th, fell six or eight inches more, so that we had a foot depth of snow','ltr_aab2502.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2503','letter','1804-02-16','New York','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','Goldsmith is the very book I should have recommended. A critical knowledge of historical events may assist a statesman or form a pedant.','ltr_aab2503.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2504','letter','1804-02-21','Baltimore','MD','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','The roads were so very bad that I sent back Sam, George, and the horses from Trenton, and came on in the mail stage \'sans valet\'.','ltr_aab2504.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2505','letter','1804-02-27','Washington','MD','US','Aaron','Burr','','Thomas','Sumter','','Yet great as is my solicitude to see your wife and child, to renew my acquaintance with you, to tender you my friendship and affection, and to claim a return, I would by no means urge a measure inconsistent with your interest.','ltr_aab2505.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2506','letter','1804-03-03','Washington','MD','US','Aaron','Burr','','Charles','Biddle','','It cannot yet be settled whether there will be commissioners to run the boundary line with Spain; but I will mention the thing to the Smiths, who still profess friendship for General Wilkinson.','ltr_aab2506.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2507','letter','1804-03-06','Washington','MD','US','Aaron','Burr','','Frederic','Vanderkemp','','It affords me great pleasure to learn that you are engaged in a literary pursuit so congenial with your taste and your talents.','ltr_aab2507.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2508','letter','1804-03-07','Washington','MD','US','Aaron','Burr','','William','Van Ness','','Friday last was the day assigned for the appearance of Judge Pickering on his impeachment. He did not appear','ltr_aab2508.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2509','letter','1804-03-28','New York','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','They are very busy here about an election between Morgan Lewis and A. Burr. The former supported by the Livingstons and Clintons, the latter \'per se\'.','ltr_aab2509.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2510','letter','1804-04-03','New York','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','The History of Frederic II. will amuse you. You will read Montesquieu with interest and instruction.','ltr_aab2510.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2511','letter','1804-04-18','New York','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','','','','Your vanity, if in any degree concerned, will be fully satisfied by the assurance that my heart, my wishes, and my thoughts will be with you.','ltr_aab2511.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2512','letter','1804-04-25','New York','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','I, too, write in a storm; an election storm, of the like you have once been a witness. The thing began yesterday, and will terminate to-morrow.','ltr_aab2512.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2513','letter','1804-05-01','New York','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','The election is lost by a great majority: \'tant mieux\'. It does not appear possible that I should make you a visit; even if La G. should not prevent it, which ought to be hoped, some other thing of like kind will.','ltr_aab2513.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2514','letter','1804-05-20','New York','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','','','','I send you a sample of that species of philosophy which I have thought particularly suited to your cast of mind and the delicacy of your taste. You are to read from the 66th page to the 125th.','ltr_aab2514.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2515','letter','1804-05-08','New York','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','The affair of La G. is becoming serious. After due reflection, this does appear to me to be the most discreet thing--prudence, cheerfulness, and good-temper are ingredients of importance. I will offer homage.','ltr_aab2515.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2516','letter','1804-06-11','New York','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','I have studied every pothook and trammel of his first literary performance, to see what rays of genius could be discovered.','ltr_aab2516.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2517','letter','1804-06-13','New York','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','Another interview yesterday with La G. One more would be fatal and final. I shall seek it to-day; \'after which\' I will read Moore\'s fables, you impudence.','ltr_aab2517.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2518','letter','1804-06-28','New York','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','To-morrow, did I say? \'Tis nowhere to be found but in the fool\'s calendar\' and yet I said \"to-morrow.\" The morrow brought me an ague in the face, which I have been nursing from that day to this, in great ill-humour.','ltr_aab2518.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2519','letter','1804-07-01','New York','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','You may recollect, and, if you do not, your husband will, that he has several times requested me to open a correspondence between him and my bookseller in London.','ltr_aab2519.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2520','letter','1804-06-18','New York','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','','','','I send for your perusal a letter signed Charles D. Cooper, which, though apparently published some time ago, has but very recently come to my knowledge.','ltr_aab2520.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2521','letter','1804-06-21','New York','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Alexander','Hamilton','','Political opposition can never absolve gentlemen from the necessity of a rigid adherence to the laws of honour and the rules of decorum. I neither claim such privilege nor indulge it in others.','ltr_aab2521.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2522','letter','1804-07-10','New York','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','Having lately written my will, and given my private letters and papers in charge to you, I have no other direction to give you on the subject but to request you to burn all such as, if by accident made public, would injure any person.','ltr_aab2522.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2523','letter','1804-07-10','New York','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Joseph','Alston','','You will find enclosed a statement of my affairs. Swartwout and Van Ness are joint executors with you and Theodosia.','ltr_aab2523.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2524','letter','1804-07-13','New York','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Joseph','Alston','','GENERAL HAMILTON died yesterday. The malignant federalists or tories, and the imbittered Clintonians, unite in endeavouring to excite public sympathy in his favour','ltr_aab2524.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2525','letter','1804-07-18','Philadelphia','PA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Joseph','Alston','','The event of which you have been advised has driven me into a sort of exile, and may terminate in an actual and permanent ostracism.','ltr_aab2525.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2526','letter','1804-07-20','Philadelphia','PA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','I shall journey somewhere within a few days, but whither is not yet decided. My heart will travel southward, and repose on the hills of Santee.','ltr_aab2526.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2527','letter','1804-07-29','Philadelphia','PA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Joseph','Alston','','Swartwout, Van Ness, and others are secreted. How long this sort of persecution may endure cannot be conjectured.','ltr_aab2527.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2528','letter','1804-08-03','Philadelphia','PA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Joseph','Alston','','I am further advised that an application has been made to Governor Lewis, of New-York, requiring him to demand me of the governor of this state, with which Lewis will most probably be obliged to comply.','ltr_aab2528.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2529','letter','1804-08-02','Philadelphia','PA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','Don\'t let me have the idea that you are dissatisfied with me a moment. I can\'t just now endure it. At another time you may play the Juno if you please.','ltr_aab2529.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2530','letter','1804-08-03','Philadelphia','PA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','I absent myself from home merely to give a little time for passions to subside, not from any apprehension of the final effects of proceedings in courts of law.','ltr_aab2530.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2531','letter','1804-08-11','Philadelphia','PA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','I shall lay a plan for meeting you somewhere, but whether I may have it in my power to visit the high hills of Santee is doubtful; I fear improbable.','ltr_aab2531.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2532','letter','1804-08-11','Philadelphia','PA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Joseph','Alston','','My plan is to visit the Floridas for five or six weeks. I have desired Theodosia to consult you whether there be any healthy point within a hundred miles or so of St. Simons at which we might meet.','ltr_aab2532.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2533','letter','1804-08-28','Hampton','GA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','I am at the house of Major Butler, comfortably settled. A very agreeable family within half a mile. My project is to go next week to Florida, which may take up a fortnight or ten days','ltr_aab2533.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2534','letter','1804-08-31','Hampton','GA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','I am now quite settled. My establishment consists of a housekeeper, cook, and chambermaid, seamstress, and two footmen.','ltr_aab2534.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2535','letter','1804-09-03','Hampton','GA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','Mr. Morse informs you that this island is forty-five miles long, and that it lies north of the mouth Altamaha, commonly spelled Alatamaha.','ltr_aab2535.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2536','letter','1804-09-15','Frederica','GA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','Having very unexpectedly procured a boat, I left my house yesterday afternoon, came hither by land, and proceed in a few minutes for St. Mary\'s.','ltr_aab2536.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2537','letter','1804-09-26','Hampton','GA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','I returned yesterday from my Florida excursion, about which I wrote you on the 15th inst. The weather prevented me from going farther than the river St. John\'s, about thirty miles from St. Augustine.','ltr_aab2537.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2538','letter','1804-10-01','Savannah','GA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','I have been this morning scouring the town and the docks in quest of ways and means to get on. There is a packet which will sail for Charleston, on Saturday','ltr_aab2538.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2539','letter','1804-10-23','Fayetteville','GA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','No more pauses, not even for weather, till Richmond, distant two hundred miles, and proposed to be travelled in five days.','ltr_aab2539.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2540','letter','1804-10-27','Warrenton','GA','US','Aaron','Burr','','','','','The morning following I started one hour before day, the moon showing us the way, and, at about seven or eight in the evening, was at Raleigh, being full fifty miles.','ltr_aab2540.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2541','letter','1804-10-31','Petersburgh','GA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Joseph','Alston','','description','ltr_aab2541.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2542','letter','1804-10-31','Richmond','VA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','Virginia is the last state, and Petersburgh the last town in the state of Virginia, in which I should have expected any open marks of hospitality and respect.','ltr_aab2542.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2543','letter','1804-11-05','Washington','MD','US','Aaron','Burr','','Joseph','Alston','','My house and furniture have been sold for about twenty-five thousand dollars. Seven or eight thousand dollars of debts remain unpaid.','ltr_aab2543.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2544','letter','1804-11-07','Washington','MD','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','But when I deliberated about writing, it was with a view to write you sense--grave sense. What a dull thing is sense. How it mars half the pleasure of life, and yet how contemptible is all that has it not.','ltr_aab2544.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2545','letter','1804-12-04','Washington','MD','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','You have doubtless heard that there has subsisted for some time a contention of a very singular nature between the states of New-York, and New-Jersey.','ltr_aab2545.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2546','letter','1804-12-15','Washington','MD','US','Aaron','Burr','','Joseph','Alston','','The trial of Judge Chace will not come on before the middle of January. He is summoned to appear the 2d January.','ltr_aab2546.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2547','letter','1804-12-31','Washington','MD','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','I propose to move my quarters to-morrow, and the confusion has already commenced, and even pervades this letter.','ltr_aab2547.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2548','letter','1805-01-15','Washington','MD','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','One motive, however, lays down at the bottom of my heart, and has scarcely, as yet, been avowed to myself. You will conjecture, and rightly, that I mean Celeste.','ltr_aab2548.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2549','letter','1805-01-28','Washington','MD','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','You treat with too much gravity the New-Jersey affair. It should be considered as a farce, and you will yet see it terminated so as to leave only ridicule and contempt to its abettors.','ltr_aab2549.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2550','letter','1805-02-23','Washington','MD','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','Your last letters are written with more correctness, and apparently with more attention than is your habit. They have amused and pleased me much.','ltr_aab2550.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2551','letter','1804-03-10','Washington','MD','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','The plan of summer operations is to go from Philadelphia, to Fort Pitt (Pittsburg,), thence through the states on each side of the Ohio.','ltr_aab2551.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2552','letter','1805-03-13','Washington','MD','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','I made a talk, as was decent and proper, to the Senate on leaving them formally. There was nothing written or prepared, except that it had been some days on my mind to say something.','ltr_aab2552.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2553','letter','1805-03-22','Philadelphia','PA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Joseph','Alston','','I am not wholly free from apprehension that you take no interest in any thing but a rice-field. Fame says that you are about to degenerate into a mere planter.','ltr_aab2553.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2554','letter','1805-03-29','Philadelphia','PA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','People who are occupied are never dull, never melancholy. I learn, then, from your letter of the 10th, that you have been a little lazy.','ltr_aab2554.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2555','letter','1805-04-10','Philadelphia','PA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','I rejoice that your nerves are in better tone, for truly, in some of your letters, I could scarcely recognise my daughter.','ltr_aab2555.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2556','letter','1805-04-30','Pittsburg','PA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','Arrived in good order yesterday. Find my boat and hands ready. The water high and weather fine. Shall set off in two hours.','ltr_aab2556.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2557','letter','1805-05-23','Lexington','KY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','I have been received with much hospitality and kindness, and could stay a month with pleasure; but General Andrew Jackson. having provided us a boat, we shall set off on Sunday, the 2d of June, to navigate down the Cumberland','ltr_aab2557.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2558','letter','1804-11-29','Washington','MD','US','Aaron','Burr','','Joseph','Alston','','The boy, too, has a relapse of the ague, a disease of all others the most fatal to the infant constitution. Great God! what sacrifices do you make, and to what end?','ltr_aab2558.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2559','letter','1807-03-27','Richmond','VA','US','Aaron','Burr','','Theodosia','Alston','','My military escort having arrived at Fredericksburgh on our way to Washington, there met a special messenger, with orders to convey me to this place.','ltr_aab2559.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2560','letter','1816-10-16','New York','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Joeseph','Alston','','At some other time I may give you, in detail, a sketch of the sad period which has elapsed since my return. For the present, it will suffice to say that my business affords me a decent support.','ltr_aab2560.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_aab2561','letter','1815-11-15','New York','NY','US','Aaron','Burr','','Joeseph','Alston','','A congressional caucus will, in the course of the ensuing month, nominate James Monroe for President of the United States, and will call on all good republicans to support the nomination.','ltr_aab2561.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 2., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
